			<p><b>Dinner for Theseus and Ariadne</b></p>
			<p><b>Date</b> 2011<br/>
			<b>Materials</b> Clay, colored slip, and clear glaze<br/>
			<b>Size</b> Plates measure approximately 8.5 inches in diameter<br/>
				
			<p>Dinner for Theseus and Ariadne tells a story as a meal is consumed. The story of Theseus and Ariadne was chosen for its ability to inspire conversation between friends and strangers, as the story involves elements of travel, personal sacrifice, challenge, and unfulfilled love. In addition to six plates, a salad bowl and quiche plate were made to hold recipes that I often share with my friends. Each piece was individually hand-thrown and trimmed on the potterâ€™s wheel.  The drawings were carved and filled in with blue and black slip.</p>
